      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Sec 5: Auditory Distress\nProlonged exposure to the night shift may result
    in mild paranoia or auditory hallucinations\n\n- Sometimes, a call is not a call.
    If the phone is ringing and you feel a sudden, paralyzing sense of dread\u2014or
    if your Caller ID scrambles in a way that feels unsafe\u2014IGNORE IT.\n\nDo
    not pick up the receiver. If you pick up a *REDACTED*, the noise will deafen
    you and a Strike will be issued. Simply sit in the dark and let it ring until
    it gives up."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: b388037b2973be74b8618f54198147ed, type: 2}
