  m_text: 'Sec 4: IT Protocols

    Our legacy systems are occasionally prone to
    aggressive, localized malware. You are responsible for your own hardware.


    If
    you answer a call and your CRT monitor begins flashing violently while unauthorized
    code types itself onto your screen, your terminal has been compromised.


    -
    Do NOT attempt to use the phone.


    - Do NOT attempt to read the text.


    -
    Press and hold the REBOOT button on your monitor until the system forces a hard
    reset.'
